# Graphify-First Search Policy (ADR-0118)

When you need to understand an unfamiliar symbol, file, or subsystem in
this repository, consult the graphify knowledge graph **before** running
`Grep`, `SemanticSearch`, or reading files at random.

1. Read `graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md` for the high-level module map,
   recent deltas, and hotspot callouts.
2. Query `graphify-out/graph.json` for symbol-level neighbourhoods
   (callers, callees, inheritance, ownership). A compact jq snippet:

   ```bash
   jq '.nodes[] | select(.name=="DirectorPolicy")' graphify-out/graph.json
   ```

3. Only after the graph has been consulted should you fall back to
   `Grep` or `SemanticSearch` — and when you do, cite the graph node id
   you expanded from in your explanation so the audit trail stays
   complete.

If `graphify-out/graph.json` is missing or stale (older than HEAD),
rebuild it from the repo root with `graphify update .` (writes/updates
`graphify-out/`) before relying on it.

Never edit `graphify-out/*` by hand; it is regenerated by the
`post-commit` and `post-checkout` hooks installed per
`tools/ai/README.md`.
